	<p>Two, possibly compound, statements A and B are considered to be <term>equivalent</term> if they have the same truth value for all inputs. This is denoted <m>A \leftrightarrow B.</m> <xref ref="demorganand" /> and <xref ref="demorganor" /> provides truth tables that show two pairs of equivalent statements known as DeMorgan's Laws.</p>

